    <div class="recipe-2">
      <div class="the-savory-umami-combination-parent">
        <div class="the-savory-umami-combination">
          The savory, umami combination of soy sauce, vinegar, and garlic
          breathes life into the classic dish we know as adobo. Who doesn’t love
          deliciously tender chunks of chicken that soak up an incredibly
          dynamic sauce? With easy, go-to components like eggs, peppercorn,
          vinegar, soy sauce and bay leaves, among others, it comes as no
          surprise that chicken adobo is a no fail meal in many Filipino homes.
          We love this dish for its vibrant flavors and addictive aroma; that
          go-to mix of salty and sweet can do no wrong! As such, there’s a
          reason why this perfect chicken adobo is heralded as a national dish!
        </div>
        <div class="group-item"></div>
        <img class="image-7-icon" alt="" src="./assets/public/image-7@2x.png" />

        <div class="group-inner"></div>
        <img class="image-8-icon" alt="" src="./assets/public/image-8@2x.png" />

        <img class="image-4-icon" alt="" src="./assets/public/image-4@2x.png" />

        <img class="image-6-icon" alt="" src="./assets/public/image-6@2x.png" />

        <div class="chicken-adobo">Chicken Adobo</div>
      </div>
      <img class="image-5-icon" alt="" src="./assets/public/image-5@2x.png" />

      <div class="ingredients-2-lbs-chicken-cut">
        <p class="instructions">Ingredients</p>
        <ul class="lbs-chicken-cut-into-serving">
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span>2 lbs. chicken cut into serving pieces</span>
          </li>
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span>1 Knorr Chicken Cube</span>
          </li>
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span>5 eggs medium size</span>
          </li>
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span>¼ cup soy sauce</span>
          </li>
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span>¼ cup vinegar</span>
          </li>
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span>1 cup water</span>
          </li>
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span>3 laurel leaves</span>
          </li>
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span>2 teaspoons whole peppercorn</span>
          </li>
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span>8 cloves garlic crushed</span>
          </li>
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span>1 teaspoon sugar</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>3 tablespoons cooking oil</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="prep-14-minutes-container">
        <p class="prep-14-minutes">Prep: 14 minutes</p>
        <p class="prep-14-minutes">Cook: 17 minutes</p>
      </div>
      <div class="instructions-combine-chicken-container">
        <p class="instructions">Instructions</p>
        <ul class="lbs-chicken-cut-into-serving">
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span
              >Combine chicken, soy sauce, vinegar, and 5 cloves garlic. Mix
              well until all ingredients are well incorporated.
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prep-14-minutes">&nbsp;</p>
        <ul class="lbs-chicken-cut-into-serving">
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span
              >Meanwhile, boil the eggs for 10 minutes. Let the eggs cool down
              afterwards and peel off the shell.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span
              >Heat oil in a pan. sauté the remaining garlic until it starts to
              turn brown.</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prep-14-minutes">&nbsp;</p>
        <ul class="lbs-chicken-cut-into-serving">
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span
              >Add the marinated chicken (do not include the marinade yet). Cook
              for 3 minutes.</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prep-14-minutes">&nbsp;</p>
        <ul class="lbs-chicken-cut-into-serving">
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span
              >Pour the remaining marinade into the pan and add water. Let
              boil.</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prep-14-minutes">&nbsp;</p>
        <ul class="lbs-chicken-cut-into-serving">
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span
              >Add bay leaves, whole peppercorn, and Knorr Chicken Cube. Stir.
              Cover the pan and continue cooking using low to medium heat for 15
              minutes.</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prep-14-minutes">&nbsp;</p>
        <ul class="lbs-chicken-cut-into-serving">
          <li class="knorr-chicken-cube">
            <span
              >Add the sugar and put the eggs into the pan. Gently stir. Cook
              for 2 minutes.</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prep-14-minutes">&nbsp;</p>
        <ul class="lbs-chicken-cut-into-serving">
          <li>
            <span
              >Transfer to a serving plate and serve along with a huge bowl of
              newly cooked rice.</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
